W. Freeland DALZELL, Libelant Appellee, v. Steam Tug MARGARET, Her Engines, etc.; Erie Basin Towing & Hoisting Company, Claimant Appellant. W. Freeland DALZELL, Libelant Appellee, v. ROBINS DRY DOCK & REPAIR COMPANY, Respondent Appellant. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 6, 1926.) No. 169. Crowell & Rouse, of New York City (E. C. Rouse, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Bigham, Englar & Jones, of New York City (L. J. Matteson, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed in open court.
